### Introduction to DevOps

What is DevOps?
1.1 DevOps in Simple Words

Imagine a software project like making a cake:

Developers = chefs (write the recipe)
Operations = waiters/kitchen staff (bake, serve, maintain the kitchen)

In the old way (traditional IT), developers wrote the recipe and threw it over the wall to operations. If something went wrong, it took a long time to fix.

DevOps = developers and operations working together all the time, using tools to automate and speed up everything.

✅ Goal: Make software faster, more reliable, and easier to update.
